## Steps

### step 1
id: open-payer-documents
instruction: From the payer detail page (use review-payer-intel flow to get there), make sure the Documents tab is active. You'll see a list of policy documents on the left.
success_criteria: The Documents tab is active and you can see a list of policy document titles.
anchor: "Documents tab"
on_success: next
on_stuck: Navigate to a payer first using the review-payer-intel flow.

### step 2
id: click-document
instruction: Click on a document title in the list to open it in the PDF viewer on the right side of the screen.
success_criteria: The document is open in the PDF viewer. A chat bar is visible at the bottom of the viewer.
anchor: "document title"
on_success: next
on_stuck: Click on any document name in the left panel list.

### step 3
id: ask-about-document
instruction: Use the chat bar at the bottom of the document viewer to ask questions directly about this policy. For example: "Does this cover CPT 99213?", "What's the timely filing deadline?", "Are modifiers required for this service?" Altair answers by referencing the exact section.
success_criteria: Altair has responded with a direct answer from the document content.
anchor: "chat bar"
on_success: completion
on_stuck: Type in the chat input at the bottom of the viewer and press Enter.

## Completion Message
you can now read payer policies without leaving altair. use the chat to ask specific coverage questions — altair cites the exact section it's pulling from. the Criteria Trees tab has structured billing rules extracted from this and other policies.

